#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "**31 JAN | Sri Lanka:** *Rebels joined other eco-activists to clean up Bellanwilla-Attidiya Wildlife Sanctuary. The wetlands are home to many endemic species and play a major role in controlling floods in the capital Colombo, but are threatened by pollution and illegal encroachment.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:163
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-02-09-newsletter-48-image10.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "*The 59 bags of collected waste were recycled or sent for [co-processing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co-processing). Sri Lankan rebels will repeat the clean up every month until the wetlands are entirely free from waste.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:167
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/b27ac3db-d8fb-4f99-bdaa-1211207310d0.jpg)"
